### 3. Required node version

This script runs using Node.js (v12+ should be fine).

**No Makefile needed.**  
If the test script needs the command to be `./minigit`, this is ready as is.

---

### 4. Quick Usage

```sh
./minigit init
./minigit add foo.txt
./minigit commit -m "First commit"
./minigit status
./minigit log
```

---

### 5. Notes

- Each commit stores a "snapshot" of file hashes (not diffs).
- Only single files added at a time (`add` does not take wildcards here).
